   Data
   Municipal datasets will consist of coverages related to emergency
   management and natural disaster situations. Data layers representing
   important natural hazards affecting each locality, as well as critical
   infrastructure, such as roads, power lines, water and energy supply etc
   are being produced.
   Project Tour
   Data gathering and preparation
   Dataset preparation
   Datasets. Vector coverages for topography, hydrography and manmade
   features are being prepared by the USGS. The coverages are being
   vectorized using maps prepared by the cooperating agencies of each
   country, and converted to DRG format by USGS personnel of the Geologic
   and Mapping divisions. Aerial photography is being converted to DOQ
   format by the USGS. Ground control points for the aerial photography
   have been gathered by USGS personnel and local authorities in the four
   countries.
   USGS local agency personnel gather control points using GPS in Puerto
   Barrios, Guatemala.
   gis gis
   Municipal Development Tool (MDT)
   Currently under development, this application is a low-cost solution
   for natural disaster mitigation and municipal management and
   development. It will allow municipal officials to manage to their
   cadastral GIS data sets, and link that information to their disaster
   management GIS database. It will also help in the assessment of damages
   after a disaster event and in planning for urban expansions and
   developments based on local susceptibility to natural hazards.
   With the MDT municipal officials and GIS users will create cadastral
   records linked to points in a coverage. The MDT keeps track of
   information about a structure's physical characteristics, and type of
   use. This data can be used to produce additional map layers to the
   municipal GIS. The use of high precision aerial photography and GPS
   data gathered locally, allows the database records to have a high
   positional accuracy, providing a precise inventory of structures and
   their uses in the municipality.
   Example of a municipal dataset showing multiple data layers.
